will get us AIR speech.&quot;  I have repeatedly been told with this method that &#39;air&#39; has 
something to do with the communication.  

Not sure what Arthur&#39;s definition of &#39;air&#39; is, but it is definitely key to what is taking place.  
He&#39;s used terms and phrases like &quot;Air-to-air&quot; - &quot;Air Ports&quot; - &quot;Air Portals&quot; - &quot;Helps you 
enter our air&quot; - &quot;They&#39;ll give you air to us&quot; - &quot;I have air&quot; etc.  MANY references.

Margaret

